HEADWORD: Idorgan
<hw>Id*or"gan</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ form + E.
<ets>organ</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>A morphological unit,
consisting of two or more plastids, which does not possess the positive
character of the person or stock, in distinction from the physiological
organ or <xex>biorgan</xex>. See <er>Morphon</er>.</def></p>

